Topic: UPI / Online Payment Fraud

Online payment fraud has become very common among college students in India due to the rapid use of digital payment apps. In a typical scenario, a student receives a phone call from someone pretending to be a bank representative. The caller informs the student that their bank account or UPI account will be blocked due to verification issues. The caller sounds professional and creates urgency to make the situation believable.

The fraudster then sends a link through SMS or WhatsApp and asks the student to click on it to “verify” the account. The link leads to a fake website that looks exactly like the real bank or payment app. The student enters confidential details such as debit card number, CVV, OTP, or UPI PIN. Within minutes, money is transferred from the victim’s bank account without their knowledge.

Students are usually targeted because they frequently use UPI apps for shopping, food delivery, and bill payments. The consequences include financial loss, mental stress, and loss of trust in digital services. Many victims feel embarrassed and delay reporting the incident, which makes recovery difficult.

This case highlights the importance of digital awareness and safe online practices to prevent financial cybercrime.
